(4, 'Melody Guitar Beginner Course', 'melody-guitar-beginner-course-4', 'Embark on a melodious journey with our online guitar learning course! Whether you\'re a complete beginner or looking to refine your skills, this comprehensive program offers step-by-step guidance to master the art of playing the guitar.', 1, 39, 'general', 1, 'core', 'active', 'beginner', 'english', 1, 0, 39, 19, 1, '', NULL, 'uploads/course-thumbnail/-1716370521.jpg', 'uploads/course-banner/-1716370522.jpg', 'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=iTlsP6RfCQ8&t=271s', '<p>Dive into the enchanting world of guitar playing with our immersive online course! Whether you\'re a complete novice or seeking to elevate your skills, our program caters to all levels of expertise. Through a carefully curated curriculum, you\'ll embark on a journey of musical discovery, mastering fundamental techniques like chord progression, strumming patterns, and fingerstyle melodies. Guided by seasoned instructors, our engaging video lessons provide comprehensive instruction, supplemented by interactive exercises to reinforce your learning. From understanding music theory to honing your improvisational skills, each module is designed to empower you with the tools and confidence to excel on the fretboard. With our supportive online community, you\'ll have the opportunity to connect with fellow learners, share experiences, and seek guidance on your musical journey. Whether you aspire to play acoustic ballads, rock anthems, or intricate jazz compositions, our course offers a structured pathway to unlock your full potential as a guitarist. Join us today and embark on a fulfilling musical odyssey from the comfort of your own home!<br></p>', '{\"0\":\"Participants will need access to either an acoustic or electric guitar for practicing and applying the lessons taught in the course. Can I learn to play specific songs in this course?\",\"2\":\"A stable internet connection is necessary to access the online course materials, including video lessons, interactive exercises, and resources.\",\"3\":\"Participants will need a computer, laptop, tablet, or smartphone with a compatible web browser to access the course platform and view the lessons.\",\"4\":\"While not mandatory, having a music stand can be beneficial for keeping course materials, such as printable chord charts and sheet music, organized and easily accessible during practice sessions.\",\"5\":\"A guitar tuner is recommended to ensure the instrument is properly tuned before practicing and playing along with lessons. Tuning apps or electronic tuners are readily available and can be used on smartphones or computers.\",\"6\":\"While not essential, a metronome can be helpful for practicing rhythm and timing exercises. Metronome apps are available for smartphones and computers, or participants can use online metronome tools.\",\"7\":\"Keeping a notebook and pen handy for jotting down notes, chord progressions, and practice schedules can aid in tracking progress and reinforcing learning.\"}', '{\"0\":\"Participants will develop proficiency in playing the guitar, mastering essential techniques such as strumming, fingerpicking, chord changes, and fretboard navigation.\",\"2\":\"Participants will gain a solid understanding of music theory concepts relevant to guitar playing, including scales, chords, rhythm, and melody. This knowledge will enable them to analyze songs, create their own music, and improvise with confidence.\",\"3\":\"Participants will expand their repertoire of songs and musical styles, learning to play a diverse range of pieces spanning various genres, including rock, pop, blues, folk, and classical music.\",\"4\":\"Through guided practice and feedback, participants will improve their technical skills, including hand coordination, dexterity, timing, and expression. They will learn to play with precision, fluidity, and musicality.\",\"5\":\"Participants will build confidence in their ability to perform in front of others, whether it\'s playing solo, accompanying singers or other musicians, or jamming with friends. They will develop stage presence, poise, and the ability to connect with an audience through their music.\",\"6\":\"Participants will unlock their creativity and express themselves through the guitar, experimenting with different sounds, textures, and musical ideas. They will learn to express emotions, tell stories, and convey meaning through their playing.\",\"7\":\"Participants will gain independence as musicians, learning to play songs by ear, improvise solos, and compose their own music. They will develop the skills to learn new songs independently, without relying solely on sheet music or tablature.\",\"8\":\"Participants will have the opportunity to collaborate with other musicians, whether through online forums, virtual jam sessions, or local music communities. They will learn to listen, communicate, and work together to create cohesive musical performances.\",\"9\":\"Completing the course will instill a passion for lifelong learning and growth as a musician. Participants will be equipped with the skills, knowledge, and resources to continue advancing their guitar playing skills independently beyond the course.\"}', '[{\"title\":\"Do I need any prior experience to enroll in this course?\",\"description\":\"No prior experience is necessary! Our course caters to beginners and those with some familiarity with the guitar. Whether you\'ve never picked up a guitar before or have some basic knowledge, our lessons are structured to accommodate learners of all levels.\"},{\"title\":\"What type of guitar do I need for this course?\",\"description\":\"You can use either an acoustic or electric guitar for our course. While there may be slight differences in techniques between the two, the fundamental principles of playing remain the same. Choose the type of guitar that resonates with your musical preferences and goals.\"},{\"title\":\"How long does it take to complete the course?\",\"description\":\"The duration of the course can vary depending on your learning pace and practice habits. On average, students complete the course within a few months, dedicating several hours per week to watching lessons, practicing, and mastering new skills.\"},{\"title\":\"Are there any additional materials or tools required for the course?\",\"description\":\"All you need is your guitar and access to a computer or mobile device with an internet connection. Supplementary materials, such as printable chord charts and music theory resources, will be provided within the course platform.\"},{\"title\":\"Will I have access to the course materials after completing the course?\",\"description\":\"es, you\'ll have lifetime access to all course materials, including video lessons, exercises, and resources. This allows you to revisit lessons, review techniques, and continue practicing even after completing the course.\"},{\"title\":\"Are there opportunities for interaction and feedback from instructors?\",\"description\":\"Absolutely! Our course features discussion forums where you can interact with instructors and fellow students, ask questions, share progress, and receive feedback on your playing. Our instructors are dedicated to supporting you throughout your learning journey.\"},{\"title\":\"Is there a certificate of completion provided?\",\"description\":\"Upon successfully completing the course requirements, including quizzes and assignments, you\'ll receive a certificate of completion. This certificate validates your achievement and can be a valuable addition to your musical credentials.\"}]', '[\"1\"]', 0, '2025-01-01 09:06:47', '2025-03-09 05:20:56', 0, '{\"lesson_completion_role\":\"percentage\",\"minimum_duration\":15,\"minimum_percentage\":\"30\",\"locked_lesson_message\":\"&lt;h3 xss=&quot;removed&quot; style=&quot;text-align: center; &quot;&gt;&lt;span xss=&quot;removed&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Permission denied!&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;p xss=&quot;removed&quot; style=&quot;text-align: center; &quot;&gt;&lt;span xss=&quot;removed&quot;&gt;This course supports drip content, so you must complete the previous lessons.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\"}', NULL),
(5, 'Complete Blender Creator: Learn 3D Modelling', 'complete-blender-creator-learn-3d-modelling-5', 'Unlock the boundless world of 3D modeling with our \'Complete Blender Creator\' course! Perfect for beginners and aspiring artists alike, this immersive program guides you through every step of mastering Blender, the industry-leading software for 3D creation.', 1, 26, 'general', 1, 'core', 'active', 'intermediate', 'english', 1, 0, 70, NULL, NULL, '', NULL, 'uploads/course-thumbnail/-1718520891.jpg', 'uploads/course-banner/-1718520891.jpg', 'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=iTlsP6RfCQ8&t=271s', '<p>Embark on a transformative journey into the realm of 3D modeling with our comprehensive \'Complete Blender Creator: Learn 3D Modelling\' course. Designed for beginners and seasoned artists alike, this immersive program equips you with the essential skills to master Blender, the industry-standard software for 3D creation. Dive deep into the intricacies of modeling, texturing, sculpting, animation, and rendering as our expert instructors guide you through each step of the creative process.</p><p><br></p><p>Through engaging video tutorials, practical exercises, and hands-on projects, you\'ll learn to sculpt lifelike characters, craft stunning environments, and design captivating objects with precision and finesse. Whether you\'re aspiring to create animated films, video games, architectural visualizations, or product designs, this course provides the foundation you need to turn your imagination into reality.</p>', '{\"0\":\"Participants will need access to a computer or laptop with sufficient processing power and memory to run Blender smoothly. Blender is compatible with Windows, macOS, and Linux operating systems.\",\"2\":\"A stable internet connection is necessary to access the online course materials, including video lessons, downloadable resources, and interactive exercises.\",\"3\":\"Participants must have Blender installed on their computer. Blender is a free and open-source 3D creation software available for download from the official Blender website (blender.org). The course is designed to be compatible with Blender 2.8 and newer versions.\",\"4\":\"Blender\'s interface is optimized for mouse navigation, so participants will need a mouse with a scroll wheel for efficient navigation and interaction with the software.\",\"5\":\"Above all, participants should approach the course with enthusiasm, curiosity, and a genuine desire to learn and improve their skills in 3D modelling. Dedication, practice, and perseverance are key to mastering Blender and creating stunning 3D models.\",\"6\":\"While no prior experience in 3D modelling is required, participants should have basic computer skills, including familiarity with operating systems, file management, and software installation.\",\"7\":\"Participants should be prepared to dedicate several hours per week to studying, practicing, and completing assignments as they progress through the course. The course is self-paced, allowing flexibility to fit learning around other commitments.\",\"8\":\"While not mandatory, participants may find it beneficial to use a graphics tablet for sculpting and digital painting exercises. Graphics tablets provide greater precision and control compared to using a mouse for certain tasks in Blender.\"}', '{\"0\":\"Participants will develop proficiency in using Blender, mastering its interface, tools, and features to create stunning 3D models, animations, and visual effects.\",\"2\":\"Participants will gain a solid understanding of fundamental 3D modelling principles, including modeling techniques, topology, UV mapping, and texturing.\",\"3\":\"Participants will learn to create complex 3D models from scratch, including objects, characters, environments, and architectural elements, using advanced modelling and sculpting techniques.\",\"4\":\"Participants will learn how to animate 3D models, rig characters, create skeletal animations, and add dynamic simulations, bringing their creations to life with movement and expression.\",\"5\":\"Participants will learn to texture their 3D models using materials, shaders, and textures, adding color, detail, and realism to their creations.\",\"6\":\"Participants will learn how to set up scenes, configure lighting, and render high-quality images and animations using Blender\'s built-in rendering engine or external renderers like Cycles and Eevee.\",\"7\":\"Participants will build a portfolio of 3D models and animations showcasing their skills and creativity, which can be used to demonstrate their proficiency to potential employers or clients.\",\"8\":\"Participants will have the opportunity to collaborate with other learners, share insights, and receive feedback on their work, fostering a supportive online community of 3D artists and enthusiasts.\",\"9\":\"Completing the course will open doors to various career opportunities in industries such as animation, visual effects, game development, architecture, product design, and advertising, where proficiency in 3D modelling is in high demand.\"}', '[{\"title\":\"Do I need any prior experience in 3D modeling to enroll in this course?\",\"description\":\"No prior experience is required! This course is designed for beginners who are new to 3D modeling as well as those looking to enhance their skills in Blender. Our comprehensive curriculum starts with the basics and gradually progresses to more advanced techniques.\"},{\"title\":\"What version of Blender does this course cover?\",\"description\":\"This course covers Blender 2.8 and newer versions. While there may be minor interface differences between versions, the fundamental concepts and techniques taught in the course remain applicable across different versions of Blender.\"},{\"title\":\"What will I learn in this course?\",\"description\":\"In this course, you\'ll learn everything you need to know to become proficient in 3D modeling using Blender. This includes modeling objects and characters, texturing, sculpting, rigging, animation, and rendering. By the end of the course, you\'ll have the skills to create stunning 3D models and animations from scratch.\"},{\"title\":\"Do I need any special hardware or software to take this course?\",\"description\":\"All you need is a computer with internet access and Blender installed. Blender is a free and open-source software available for Windows, Mac, and Linux. You\'ll also need a mouse with a scroll wheel, as Blender\'s interface is optimized for mouse navigation.\"},{\"title\":\"Will I receive a certificate upon completing the course?\",\"description\":\"Yes, upon successfully completing all course requirements, including quizzes, assignments, and projects, you\'ll receive a certificate of completion. This certificate validates your achievement and can be a valuable addition to your portfolio or resume.\"},{\"title\":\"How long does it take to complete the course?\",\"description\":\"The course is self-paced, so the duration varies depending on your learning pace and schedule. On average, students complete the course within a few weeks to a few months, dedicating a few hours per week to studying and practicing Blender.\"},{\"title\":\"Is there a community or forum for students to interact and seek help?\",\"description\":\"Yes, enrolled students have access to a dedicated online community or forum where they can interact with instructors and fellow learners, ask questions, share insights, and receive feedback on their work.\"}]', '[\"1\"]', 0, '2025-01-01 09:06:47', '2025-03-09 05:21:14', 0, '{\"lesson_completion_role\":\"percentage\",\"minimum_duration\":15,\"minimum_percentage\":\"30\",\"locked_lesson_message\":\"&lt;h3 xss=&quot;removed&quot; style=&quot;text-align: center; &quot;&gt;&lt;span xss=&quot;removed&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Permission denied!&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;p xss=&quot;removed&quot; style=&quot;text-align: center; &quot;&gt;&lt;span xss=&quot;removed&quot;&gt;This course supports drip content, so you must complete the previous lessons.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\"}', NULL),
(6, 'Introduction to Abode Illustrator Essentials', 'introduction-to-abode-illustrator-essentials-6', 'In this tutorial we\'re going to draw from this drawing that I\'ve made. Just to make it simple, so we can all follow along. What I\'d like to do is, in Illustrator we\'re going to go to \'File\', \'New\'. Pick a document size, I\'m going to start with \'Print\'.', 1, 8, 'general', 1, 'core', 'active', 'beginner', 'english', 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', NULL, 'uploads/course-thumbnail/-1718282691.jpg', 'uploads/course-banner/-1716373220.jpg', 'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=iTlsP6RfCQ8&t=271s', '<p>Unlock your creative potential with our \'Introduction to Adobe Illustrator Essentials\' online course! This comprehensive program is designed for beginners and aspiring graphic designers looking to master the fundamentals of Adobe Illustrator, the industry-standard vector graphics software. Through a series of engaging video tutorials and hands-on projects, you\'ll learn how to navigate the Illustrator interface, create and manipulate shapes, use the pen tool, apply colors and gradients, and design stunning graphics with precision and ease.</p><p><br></p><p>Our expert instructors will guide you through each step of the learning process, from understanding basic vector design principles to creating complex illustrations and logos. You’ll gain practical skills in drawing, typography, and layout that are essential for any graphic design project. By the end of the course, you’ll be able to create professional-quality designs for print and digital media, including logos, icons, infographics, and more.</p><p><br></p><p>Join our vibrant online community to share your work, receive feedback, and collaborate with fellow learners. With lifetime access to course materials, you can learn at your own pace and revisit lessons anytime. Start your journey today and transform your creative ideas into reality with Adobe Illustrator!\"</p>', '{\"0\":\"Participants need to have Adobe Illustrator installed on their computer. Adobe offers a free trial, and subscription plans are available on the Adobe website.\",\"2\":\"Ensure your computer meets the minimum system requirements for Adobe Illustrator.\",\"3\":\"Adobe Illustrator is compatible with both Windows and macOS. Ensure your operating system is up to date and supported by Adobe Illustrator.\",\"4\":\"A reliable internet connection is necessary for downloading course materials, streaming video lessons, and participating in any online discussions or forums.\",\"5\":\"While a mouse is sufficient, using a graphics tablet can provide more precision and control, especially for detailed drawing and design work.\",\"6\":\"Participants should be comfortable with basic computer operations, including file management, installing software, and navigating the web.\",\"7\":\"A genuine interest in learning graphic design and vector illustration is essential. Dedication and regular practice will be key to mastering the skills taught in the course.\",\"8\":\"Keeping a notebook for jotting down notes, ideas, and sketches can be helpful for reinforcing learning and planning design projects.\",\"9\":\"To ensure clear audio during video lessons, participants should have a reliable pair of headphones or speakers.\"}', '{\"0\":\"Participants will develop a strong proficiency in using Adobe Illustrator, mastering its interface, tools, and features to create professional-quality vector graphics.\",\"2\":\"Participants will learn essential graphic design principles, including color theory, typography, and layout, enabling them to create visually appealing and effective designs.\",\"3\":\"Participants will be able to create and manipulate vector shapes, use the pen tool with confidence, and apply various drawing techniques to produce complex illustrations and designs.\",\"4\":\"Participants will gain the skills to design logos and icons, understanding the process from conceptualization to final execution, ensuring scalability and versatility of their designs.\",\"5\":\"Participants will learn how to effectively use text and typography in their designs, mastering text formatting, alignment, and creating custom typographic designs.\",\"6\":\"Participants will understand how to apply and manipulate colors, gradients, and patterns in their designs, enhancing their ability to create vibrant and dynamic artwork.\",\"7\":\"Participants will be able to create various forms of digital artwork, including posters, flyers, infographics, and web graphics, using Illustrator\\u2019s powerful tools and features.\",\"8\":\"Participants will learn how to properly export their Illustrator files for different media, including print, web, and social media, ensuring high-quality results.\",\"9\":\"Through hands-on projects and assignments, participants will build a portfolio of work demonstrating their skills and creativity, which can be used to showcase their abilities to potential clients or employers.\"}', '[{\"title\":\"Do I need any prior experience with graphic design to enroll in this course?\",\"description\":\"No prior experience is required! This course is designed for beginners and will guide you through the basics of Adobe Illustrator and vector graphic design from the ground up.\"},{\"title\":\"What software do I need for this course?\",\"description\":\"You will need Adobe Illustrator installed on your computer. Adobe offers a free trial of Illustrator, which you can use if you don\\u2019t already have a subscription.\"},{\"title\":\"What type of computer do I need to run Adobe Illustrator?\",\"description\":\"Adobe Illustrator runs on both Windows and macOS. Ensure your computer meets the minimum system requirements specified by Adobe, which typically includes a modern processor, sufficient RAM, and adequate storage space.\"},{\"title\":\"Will I receive a certificate upon completion of the course?\",\"description\":\"Yes, upon successfully completing all course modules and assignments, you will receive a certificate of completion. This can be a valuable addition to your resume or portfolio.\"},{\"title\":\"How long will it take to complete the course?\",\"description\":\"The course is self-paced, allowing you to learn at your own speed. On average, students complete the course within 4-6 weeks, dedicating a few hours per week to lessons and practice.\"},{\"title\":\"s there a community or forum for student interaction?\",\"description\":\"Yes, you will have access to an online community where you can interact with instructors and fellow students, share your work, ask questions, and receive feedback.\"},{\"title\":\"Are there any additional materials or tools required for the course?\",\"description\":\"Aside from Adobe Illustrator and a computer, you might find it helpful to have a graphic tablet for more precise drawing, though it\'s not mandatory. Additionally, a notebook for jotting down notes and ideas can be useful.\"},{\"title\":\"Can I access the course materials after completion?\",\"description\":\"Yes, you will have lifetime access to all course materials, including video lessons, project files, and resources. This allows you to revisit and review content whenever you need.\"}]', '[\"1\"]', 0, '2025-01-01 09:06:47', '2025-03-16 07:56:22', 0, '{\"lesson_completion_role\":\"percentage\",\"minimum_duration\":15,\"minimum_percentage\":\"30\",\"locked_lesson_message\":\"&lt;h3 xss=&quot;removed&quot; style=&quot;text-align: center; &quot;&gt;&lt;span xss=&quot;removed&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Permission denied!&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;p xss=&quot;removed&quot; style=&quot;text-align: center; &quot;&gt;&lt;span xss=&quot;removed&quot;&gt;This course supports drip content, so you must complete the previous lessons.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\"}', NULL),
(7, 'Basic of UI/UX', 'basic-of-ui-ux-7', 'Discover the fundamentals of user interface (UI) and user experience (UX) design with our \'Basics of UI/UX\' online course! This beginner-friendly program introduces you to the essential principles and practices of creating intuitive, user-centered digital products.', 1, 13, 'general', 1, 'elective', 'active', 'beginner', 'english', 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', NULL, 'uploads/course-thumbnail/-1718474482.jpg', 'uploads/course-banner/-1718474482.jpg', 'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=iTlsP6RfCQ8&t=271s', '<p>Unlock the foundational skills needed to excel in user interface (UI) and user experience (UX) design with our \'Basics of UI/UX\' online course. Designed for beginners and aspiring designers, this comprehensive program offers an in-depth introduction to the principles and practices essential for creating intuitive and user-friendly digital products. Through a blend of engaging video lessons, interactive exercises, and hands-on projects, you will learn to conduct user research, develop personas, create wireframes, design prototypes, and perform usability testing.</p><p><br></p><p>Our expert instructors will guide you through the entire design process, from understanding user needs to crafting seamless interactions and visually appealing interfaces. You’ll gain practical skills in tools like Sketch, Figma, or Adobe XD, and learn to apply design thinking methodologies to solve real-world problems. By the end of the course, you’ll be equipped with the knowledge and skills to design effective, user-centered interfaces for websites, mobile apps, and more.</p><p><br></p><p>Join our supportive online community, share your progress, receive feedback, and collaborate with fellow learners. With lifetime access to course materials, you can learn at your own pace and revisit lessons as needed. Start your journey in UI/UX design today and create impactful digital experiences that users will love!\"</p>', '{\"0\":\"Participants will need access to a computer or laptop with internet connectivity to access the course materials and complete assignments.\",\"2\":\"Participants will need access to design software such as Sketch, Figma, Adobe XD, or similar tools used for UI\\/UX design. These tools may offer free trials or free versions suitable for the duration of the course.\",\"3\":\"A stable internet connection is necessary for streaming video lessons, accessing online resources, participating in discussions, and submitting assignments.\",\"4\":\"Participants should have a modern web browser installed, such as Google Chrome, Mozilla Firefox, Safari, or Microsoft Edge, for accessing the course platform and materials.\",\"5\":\"While no specific technical skills are required, participants should be comfortable using a computer and navigating software applications. Familiarity with basic computer operations, such as file management, browsing, and downloading, is beneficial.\",\"6\":\"A passion for design and a desire to learn about user interface and user experience principles are essential for success in this course. Participants should be motivated to engage with the course content and apply their learning to practical projects.\",\"7\":\"Having a notebook and pen or digital note-taking tools available can be helpful for jotting down important concepts, ideas, and insights during the course.\"}', '{\"0\":\"Participants will gain a solid understanding of the fundamental principles of user interface (UI) and user experience (UX) design, including usability, accessibility, and user-centered design.\",\"2\":\"Participants will learn to use industry-standard design tools such as Sketch, Figma, or Adobe XD to create wireframes, prototypes, and mockups for digital products.\",\"3\":\"Participants will develop skills in conducting user research, including gathering user feedback, creating user personas, and identifying user needs and pain points.\",\"4\":\"Participants will learn to create wireframes and prototypes that effectively communicate the structure, layout, and functionality of digital interfaces, enabling efficient iteration and feedback.\",\"5\":\"Participants will gain practical skills in visual design principles, typography, color theory, and interaction design, enhancing the aesthetic appeal and usability of digital products.\",\"6\":\"Participants will learn how to conduct usability tests to evaluate the effectiveness and usability of digital interfaces, identify usability issues, and iterate on designs based on user feedback.\",\"7\":\"Participants will develop problem-solving and critical thinking skills, learning to analyze design problems, generate creative solutions, and make informed design decisions.\",\"8\":\"Participants will build a portfolio of UI\\/UX design projects showcasing their skills and creativity, which can be used to demonstrate their abilities to potential employers or clients.\",\"9\":\"Participants will learn how to effectively collaborate with stakeholders, developers, and other team members, communicating design ideas and concepts clearly and persuasively.\",\"10\":\"Completing the course will enhance participants\' qualifications for roles in UI\\/UX design, product design, web design, and related fields, providing a strong foundation for further professional development and career advancement.\"}', '[{\"title\":\"Do I need any prior experience in design to take this course?\",\"description\":\"No prior design experience is required. This course is designed for beginners who are new to UI\\/UX design, as well as those looking to enhance their foundational skills.\"},{\"title\":\"What software will I need for this course?\",\"description\":\"You will need access to design tools such as Sketch, Figma, or Adobe XD. These tools offer free trials or free versions, which are suitable for the duration of the course.\"},{\"title\":\"How long does the course take to complete?\",\"description\":\"The course is self-paced, so the duration depends on your learning speed and schedule. On average, students complete the course within 4-6 weeks, dedicating a few hours per week.\"},{\"title\":\"Will I receive a certificate upon completion?\",\"description\":\"Yes, upon successfully completing all course modules and assignments, you will receive a certificate of completion. This can be a valuable addition to your portfolio or resume.\"},{\"title\":\"Is there any support available if I encounter difficulties?\",\"description\":\"Yes, you will have access to a dedicated support team and instructors who can assist you with any questions or difficulties you encounter during the course.\"},{\"title\":\"What kind of projects will I work on during the course?\",\"description\":\"You will work on various hands-on projects that include creating user personas, wireframes, prototypes, and performing usability tests. These projects will help you apply the concepts you learn and build a portfolio of work.\"},{\"title\":\"How will this course benefit my career?\",\"description\":\"This course will equip you with essential UI\\/UX design skills that are highly valued in the tech industry. You\'ll be prepared for roles such as UI\\/UX designer, product designer, and more, with a strong foundation to further develop your expertise.\"},{\"title\":\"Can I interact with other students?\",\"description\":\"Yes, you can interact with other students through our online community forums. This is a great place to share your work, receive feedback, and collaborate on projects.\"},{\"title\":\"Do I need a specific type of computer to take this course?\",\"description\":\"Any modern computer with internet access should be sufficient. Ensure your computer meets the system requirements for the design software you choose to use Figma.\"}]', '[\"1\"]', 0, '2025-01-01 09:06:47', '2025-03-13 05:29:16', 0, '{\"lesson_completion_role\":\"percentage\",\"minimum_duration\":15,\"minimum_percentage\":\"30\",\"locked_lesson_message\":\"&lt;h3 