lies to any fields of art and design: Once you know what color does and how you can use it to your advantage, you win!</p><p style=\"margin-top: 0.8rem; max-width: 118.4rem; font-family: &quot;Udemy Sans&quot;, &quot;SF Pro Text&quot;, -apple-system, &quot;system-ui&quot;, Roboto, &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif, &quot;Apple Color Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Symbol&quot;;\">And with this course I want to guide you there.</p><p style=\"margin-top: 0.8rem; max-width: 118.4rem; font-family: &quot;Udemy Sans&quot;, &quot;SF Pro Text&quot;, -apple-system, &quot;system-ui&quot;, Roboto, &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif, &quot;Apple Color Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Symbol&quot;;\"><br></p><p style=\"margin-top: 0.8rem; max-width: 118.4rem; font-family: &quot;Udemy Sans&quot;, &quot;SF Pro Text&quot;, -apple-system, &quot;system-ui&quot;, Roboto, &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif, &quot;Apple Color Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Symbol&quot;;\"><strong>Style:</strong></p><p style=\"margin-top: 0.8rem; max-width: 118.4rem; font-family: &quot;Udemy Sans&quot;, &quot;SF Pro Text&quot;, -apple-system, &quot;system-ui&quot;, Roboto, &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif, &quot;Apple Color Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Symbol&quot;;\">- calm &amp; precise</p><p style=\"margin-top: 0.8rem; max-width: 118.4rem; font-family: &quot;Udemy Sans&quot;, &quot;SF Pro Text&quot;, -apple-system, &quot;system-ui&quot;, Roboto, &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif, &quot;Apple Color Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Symbol&quot;;\">- occasional dry jokes</p><p style=\"margin-top: 0.8rem; max-width: 118.4rem; font-family: &quot;Udemy Sans&quot;, &quot;SF Pro Text&quot;, -apple-system, &quot;system-ui&quot;, Roboto, &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif, &quot;Apple Color Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Symbol&quot;;\">- many examples and visuals</p><p style=\"margin-top: 0.8rem; max-width: 118.4rem; font-family: &quot;Udemy Sans&quot;, &quot;SF Pro Text&quot;, -apple-system, &quot;system-ui&quot;, Roboto, &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif, &quot;Apple Color Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Symbol&quot;;\"><br></p><p style=\"margin-top: 0.8rem; max-width: 118.4rem; font-family: &quot;Udemy Sans&quot;, &quot;SF Pro Text&quot;, -apple-system, &quot;system-ui&quot;, Roboto, &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif, &quot;Apple Color Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Symbol&quot;;\">Watch the video lessons, take some notes if you like and participate in the class project, and you will soon not have to worry about colors anymore, but use them with competence and confidence!</p><div><br></div></div>', '{\"0\":\"No programming experience is required, but a basic understanding of HTML will be helpful.\",\"2\":\"A computer that you are allowed to install software on, and an internet connection.\"}', '{\"0\":\"The PHP language itself\",\"2\":\"How to keep your code organized (we actually take the time to understand the MVC pattern)\",\"3\":\"How to setup your personal computer for Laravel practice\",\"4\":\"How to deploy your app up to the web (both local Docker practice, and a real public Linux VPS)\"}', '[{\"title\":\"Who is this course for?\",\"description\":\"This course is tailored for beginners who are new to Laravel and want to learn how to build web applications using this powerful PHP framework.\"},{\"title\":\"Do I need any prior programming knowledge before taking this course?\",\"description\":\"Basic understanding of PHP is recommended. Familiarity with HTML, CSS, and basic programming concepts will be beneficial but is not required.\"},{\"title\":\"What will I be able to do after completing this course?\",\"description\":\"By the end of this course, you will be able to set up a Laravel development environment, understand the fundamentals of Laravel, and build simple web applications from scratch.\"},{\"title\":\"How is this course structured?\",\"description\":\"The course is divided into clear, easy-to-follow modules that cover essential topics such as setting up Laravel, understanding MVC architecture, routing, controllers, views, and database interactions. Each module includes video tutorials, hands-on exercises, and quizzes.\"},{\"title\":\"What resources are provided in this course?\",\"description\":\"You will have access to comprehensive video lectures, downloadable code samples, practical exercises, and quizzes to test your understanding. Additionally, there will be a community forum for support and discussion.\"},{\"title\":\"How long will I have access to the course materials?\",\"description\":\"Once you enroll, you will have lifetime access to the course materials, including any future updates or additional content.\"},{\"title\":\"What if I have questions or need help during the course?\",\"description\":\"You can ask questions and seek help through the course\\u2019s Q&A section or community forum, where instructors and fellow students can provide assistance and guidance.\"},{\"title\":\"Can I work on the course at my own pace?\",\"description\":\"Yes, the course is designed to be self-paced, allowing you to learn and progress at your own speed. You can revisit and review the materials as often as needed.\"},{\"title\":\"Will I work on any projects during the course?\",\"description\":\"Yes, you will work on several small projects throughout the course that will help you apply the concepts learned and build practical experience in Laravel development.\"}]', '[\"1\"]', 0, '2025-01-01 09:06:47', '2025-01-01 09:06:47', 0, '{\"lesson_completion_role\":\"percentage\",\"minimum_duration\":15,\"minimum_percentage\":\"30\",\"locked_lesson_message\":\"&lt;h3 xss=&quot;removed&quot; style=&quot;text-align: center; &quot;&gt;&lt;span xss=&quot;removed&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Permission denied!&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;p xss=&quot;removed&quot; style=&quot;text-align: center; &quot;&gt;&lt;span xss=&quot;removed&quot;&gt;This course supports drip content, so you must complete the previous lessons.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\"}', NULL),
(260, 'Logo Design Mastery In Adobe Illustrator', 'logo-design-mastery-in-adobe-illustrator-260', 'Learn Logo Design Theory, The Creative Process, How to Work With Clients & Master Adobe Illustrator Tools', 1, 10, 'general', NULL, NULL, 'active', 'intermediate', 'hindi', 1, 0, 59, 45, 1, '', NULL, 'uploads/course-thumbnail/-1722153292.jpg', 'uploads/course-banner/-1722319502.jpg', NULL, '<p style=\"max-width: 118.4rem; color: rgb(45, 47, 49); font-family: &quot;Udemy Sans&quot;, &quot;SF Pro Text&quot;, -apple-system, &quot;system-ui&quot;, Roboto, &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif, &quot;Apple Color Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Symbol&quot;;\"><strong>NEW!&nbsp;September 2022 - A 100+ page downloadable PDF Guide to&nbsp;Logo&nbsp;Design Theory!&nbsp;</strong></p><p style=\"margin-top: 0.8rem; max-width: 118.4rem; color: rgb(45, 47, 49); font-family: &quot;Udemy Sans&quot;, &quot;SF Pro Text&quot;, -apple-system, &quot;system-ui&quot;, Roboto, &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif, &quot;Apple Color Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Symbol&quot;;\"><strong>NEW!&nbsp;May 2021 - A Client Presentation Template in&nbsp;Adobe Illustrator&nbsp;<br><br>This powerful extensive class</strong>&nbsp;trains you in&nbsp;<strong>all aspects of the logo design process&nbsp;</strong>including logo design&nbsp;<strong>theory, execution, working with typography, selecting color pallets, preparing</strong>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<strong>exporting&nbsp;</strong>files and&nbsp;<strong>how to work with adobe illustrator to create stunning logos.</strong></p><p style=\"margin-top: 0.8rem; max-width: 118.4rem; color: rgb(45, 47, 49); font-family: &quot;Udemy Sans&quot;, &quot;SF Pro Text&quot;, -apple-system, &quot;system-ui&quot;, Roboto, &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif, &quot;Apple Color Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Symbol&quot;;\">Not only that this class teaches you how to&nbsp;<strong>work with clients&nbsp;</strong>by following several&nbsp;<strong>full logo design projects from start to finish</strong>. We talk about what type of questions to ask clients before starting your logo design process.<br><br>We also apply our&nbsp;<strong>logos to mockups</strong>&nbsp;so we can create&nbsp;<strong>polished presentations for our portfolio&nbsp;</strong>or to the client for approval. We even talk about where to find possible clients by following a step by step process.</p><p style=\"margin-top: 0.8rem; max-width: 118.4rem; color: rgb(45, 47, 49); font-family: &quot;Udemy Sans&quot;, &quot;SF Pro Text&quot;, -apple-system, &quot;system-ui&quot;, Roboto, &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif, &quot;Apple Color Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Symbol&quot;;\">For the&nbsp;<strong>theory section&nbsp;</strong>of this course we dive into logo design categories and also review all the different logo design styles while showing stellar examples of each.<br><br>I go over the&nbsp;<strong>characteristics of strong logos designs&nbsp;</strong>and walk you through these using real world companies. Lastly, we cannot talk about logo design theory without talking about the power of color as we review the color psychology chart.</p><p style=\"margin-top: 0.8rem; max-width: 118.4rem; color: rgb(45, 47, 49); font-family: &quot;Udemy Sans&quot;, &quot;SF Pro Text&quot;, -apple-system, &quot;system-ui&quot;, Roboto, &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif, &quot;Apple Color Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Symbol&quot;;\">The next section is for those who need a&nbsp;<strong>crash course in Adobe illustrator&nbsp;</strong>as we review all of the most used tools we will use throughout this class including the width, shape-builder, offset path, gradient tools and using layering masks and more.<br><br>Afterwards we walk through the&nbsp;<strong>entire logo design process from scratch.</strong>&nbsp;We will learn how to quickly get our ideas out on paper, and then turn those rough ideas into real workable designs we can present to the client. We will walk through each step of the journey as we work finding those final concepts to present. We will create a mood board to find our perfect color matches and finish off our logo with the final touches.<br><br>Our next section dives deep into the<strong>&nbsp;golden ratio in logo design.</strong>&nbsp;We will create from scratch the golden ratio spiral and create the golden ratio circles we need to start to adapt our designs to the golden ratio. We will do several practice projects as well.<br><br>We then take this logo all the way through to the end including create all variations and sizes we will need to adapt this logo to just about anything. We will also create polished designs by learning how to use photoshop mock-ups. We will then use our downloadable&nbsp;<strong>file export guide</strong>&nbsp;to learn how and why we export the specific files to our clients.<br><br>The next section goes over&nbsp;<strong>portfolio building basics</strong>&nbsp;and several places and steps to find clients and to get client referrals so you can start building your design business.</p><p style=\"margin-top: 0.8rem; max-width: 118.4rem; color: rgb(45, 47, 49); font-family: &quot;Udemy Sans&quot;, &quot;SF Pro Text&quot;, -apple-system, &quot;system-ui&quot;, Roboto, &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif, &quot;Apple Color Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Symbol&quot;;\"><strong>This course is packed full of downloadable resources</strong>&nbsp;including a client questioner document, Logo styles and categories cheat sheet, color wheel and color psychology documents, a finding client’s resource, and file export, a golden ratio cheat sheet, a font paring guide and much more!<br><br><strong>This class is extensive but is gentle and paced well enough for beginners to work through the course.&nbsp;</strong>There are both beginner and intermediate level topics discussed with some advanced topics discussed later on in the course.</p><p style=\"margin-top: 0.8rem; max-width: 118.4rem; color: rgb(45, 47, 49); font-family: &quot;Udemy Sans&quot;, &quot;SF Pro Text&quot;, -apple-system, &quot;system-ui&quot;, Roboto, &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif, &quot;Apple Color Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Symbol&quot;;\">This will be for anyone interested in working through a course that has a&nbsp;<strong>deep focus on logo design or any designer who wants to fine tune their logo design and presentation skills.</strong></p><p style=\"margin-top: 0.8rem; max-width: 118.4rem; color: rgb(45, 47, 49); font-family: &quot;Udemy Sans&quot;, &quot;SF Pro Text&quot;, -apple-system, &quot;system-ui&quot;, Roboto, &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif, &quot;Apple Color Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Symbol&quot;;\">So, are you ready to up your logo design game? Let’s get started!</p>', '{\"0\":\"Familiarity with HTML, CSS, and JavaScript.\",\"2\":\"Basic knowledge of PHP is recommended but not mandatory.\",\"3\":\"A computer (Windows, macOS, or Linux) with internet access.\",\"4\":\"A code editor such as Visual Studio Code, Sublime Text, or PHPStorm.\",\"5\":\"A local development environment such as XAMPP, MAMP, or Laravel Homestead.\",\"6\":\"Composer, the PHP dependency manager, installed on your system.\",\"7\":\"Any modern web browser such as Google Chrome, Mozilla Firefox, or Safari.\",\"8\":\"A proactive attitude and readiness to engage with the course material and exercises.\"}', '{\"0\":\"You can expect to know all the fundamentals of Laravel\",\"2\":\"Routing\",\"3\":\"Controllers\",\"4\":\"Views\",\"5\":\"Cookies\",\"6\":\"Database, Migrations, Seeding, Relationships. Query Building, ORM and much more\",\"7\":\"You will learn all the latest features of Laravel\",\"8\":\"Middleware\",\"9\":\"Responses\",\"10\":\"Sessions\",\"11\":\"Validation\"}', '[{\"title\":\"Who is this course designed for?\",\"description\":\"This course is designed for anyone interested in learning Laravel, from complete beginners with no prior experience in web development to those with basic PHP knowledge looking to master Laravel.\"},{\"title\":\"What prerequisites do I need before taking this course?\",\"description\":\"Basic understanding of web development (HTML, CSS, JavaScript) and some familiarity with PHP is recommended. No prior experience with Laravel is necessary.\"},{\"title\":\"What will I learn in this course?\",\"description\":\"You will learn everything from setting up a Laravel development environment to building and deploying advanced web applications. Topics include MVC architecture, routing, controllers, views, Eloquent ORM, authentication, authorization, RESTful APIs, and more.\"},{\"title\":\"How long will it take to complete the course?\",\"description\":\"The course is self-paced, so the duration depends on your schedule and learning speed. On average, students can expect to spend several weeks to a few months completing the course and mastering the content.\"},{\"title\":\"What resources are included in the course?\",\"description\":\"The course includes video lectures, downloadable resources, practical exercises, quizzes, and real-world projects. Additionally, you will have access to a community forum for support and collaboration.\"},{\"title\":\"Will I receive a certificate upon completion?\",\"description\":\"Yes, you will receive a certificate of completion after successfully finishing the course, which you can share with potential employers or on professional networking sites.\"},{\"title\":\"How can I get help if I have questions or need assistance?\",\"description\":\"You can ask questions and seek assistance through the course\\u2019s Q&A section or community forum, where instructors and fellow students can provide guidance and support.\"},{\"title\":\"Can I access the course materials after completing the course?\",\"description\":\"Yes, once you enroll, you will have lifetime access to all course materials, including any future updates.\"},{\"title\":\"Is this course suitable for someone with no programming experience?\",\"description\":\"While basic programming knowledge is helpful, this course is designed to be accessible to complete beginners. The course starts with fundamental concepts and gradually progresses to more advanced topics.\"},{\"title\":\"Are there any projects or hands-on exercises in the course?\",\"description\":\"Yes, the course includes numerous hands-on exercises and real-world projects to help you apply the concepts learned and build practical experience in Laravel development.\"}]', '[\"1\"]', 0, '2025-01-01 09:06:47', '2025-01-01 09:06:47', 0, '{\"lesson_completion_role\":\"percentage\",\"minimum_duration\":15,\"minimum_percentage\":\"30\",\"locked_lesson_message\":\"&lt;h3 xss=&quot;removed&quot; style=&quot;text-align: center; &quot;&gt;&lt;span xss=&quot;removed&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Permission denied!&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;p xss=&quot;removed&quot; style=&quot;text-align: center; &quot;&gt;&lt;span xss=&quot;removed&quot;&gt;This course supports drip content, so you must complete the previous lessons.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\"}', NULL);
