(261, 'The Complete Drawing Masterclass: From Beginner to Advanced', 'the-complete-drawing-masterclass-from-beginner-to-advanced-261', 'Apply the art and practice of the fundamental skill of drawing, to bring your drawings to life in this ultimate course.', 1, 9, 'general', NULL, NULL, 'active', 'advanced', 'english', 1, 0, 69, 49, 1, '', NULL, 'uploads/course-thumbnail/-1722153392.jpg', 'uploads/course-banner/-1722319618.jpg', NULL, '<p style=\"font-size: inherit; max-width: 118.4rem;\">Welcome to the complete drawing masterclass! In this online drawing course, you will go from beginner to advanced, by learning in various drawing projects.</p><p style=\"margin-top: 0.8rem; font-size: inherit; max-width: 118.4rem;\">You will learn new drawing techniques, and build upon your drawing skills, to produce beautiful, amazing drawings.</p><p style=\"margin-top: 0.8rem; font-size: inherit; max-width: 118.4rem;\">This course is your opportunity to advance in your career, whether you work in animation, logo design, graphic design, architecture, fashion design, video game character design, or ANY field that uses visual storytelling, such as marketing, public speaking, and more.</p><p style=\"margin-top: 0.8rem; font-size: inherit; max-width: 118.4rem;\">Or, you simply want to draw for fun!</p><p style=\"margin-top: 0.8rem; font-size: inherit; max-width: 118.4rem;\">By the time you complete this drawing course, you will have produced a portfolio of amazing drawings, including professional landscape drawings, accurate portrait drawings, artistic still life drawings, and much, much more.</p><p style=\"margin-top: 0.8rem; font-size: inherit; max-width: 118.4rem;\"><strong>Once you enroll in this course, you get:</strong></p><ul style=\"margin-top: 0.8rem; padding-left: 2.4rem; font-size: inherit; max-width: 118.4rem;\"><li style=\"padding-left: 0.8rem;\"><p style=\"font-size: inherit; max-width: 118.4rem;\"><strong>Lifetime access to all of the content, including over 19 hours of on-demand, helpful video demonstrations and instruction.</strong></p></li><li style=\"margin-top: 0.4rem; padding-left: 0.8rem;\"><p style=\"font-size: inherit; max-width: 118.4rem;\"><strong>Various PDF&nbsp;handouts and support files.</strong></p></li><li style=\"margin-top: 0.4rem; padding-left: 0.8rem;\"><p style=\"font-size: inherit; max-width: 118.4rem;\"><strong>Access to our exclusive Drawing Club forum, for helpful feedback and critique from peers and me, the instructor of this course, Jonathan Simon.</strong></p></li></ul><p style=\"margin-top: 0.8rem; font-size: inherit; max-width: 118.4rem;\">The sections in this drawing course build upon each other, to help you master the art of drawing:</p><p style=\"margin-top: 0.8rem; font-size: inherit; max-width: 118.4rem;\"><strong>Gesture Drawing</strong>&nbsp;- You will quickly and easily learn the useful technique of gesture drawing, where we aim to capture the essence of subjects. Projects include drawing various objects, animals, and landscapes.</p><p style=\"margin-top: 0.8rem; font-size: inherit; max-width: 118.4rem;\"><strong>Drawing Materials</strong>&nbsp;- Next, after you get started drawing, we go into more detail to explain various mark making, erasing, and blending techniques, as well as various drawing tools. However, if you only have a pencil and paper, that is fine for the projects in this course.</p><p style=\"margin-top: 0.8rem; font-size: inherit; max-width: 118.4rem;\"><strong>Line and Contour Drawing</strong>&nbsp;- Learn various line drawing techniques, including contour, cross contour, and line drawing, as well as various exercises to practice hand-eye coordination and the portrayal of form and outline.</p><p style=\"margin-top: 0.8rem; font-size: inherit; max-width: 118.4rem;\"><strong>Structural Drawing</strong>&nbsp;- Learn how to produce various shapes (e.g., cylinder, cone, cube) that can be used to build more complicated structures. Draw organic objects using structural drawing, in order to draw a still life.</p><p style=\"margin-top: 0.8rem; font-size: inherit; max-width: 118.4rem;\"><strong>Tone or Value in Drawing</strong>&nbsp;- Learn how to add accurate lighting and shadows in drawings, including various techniques, including hatching, cross-hatching, and reductive or wipe out techniques, to add form and depth in drawings.</p><p style=\"margin-top: 0.8rem; font-size: inherit; max-width: 118.4rem;\"><strong>Drawing in Perspective</strong>&nbsp;- Learn various ways to show depth in drawings, such as chiaroscuro method, atmospheric perspective technique, and many more. Learn how to draw in one-point, two-point, and three-point perspective, for realistic perspective, so you can draw city scenes or other scenes from your imagination.</p><p style=\"margin-top: 0.8rem; font-size: inherit; max-width: 118.4rem;\"><strong>Block-In Drawing Method</strong>&nbsp;- This is the drawing method that I&nbsp;learned after my BFA and MFA, from another artist. It\'s the most requested drawing method I&nbsp;get from students. In this course, you will learn how to produce a detailed, rendered drawing of a still life, by using this technique.</p><p style=\"margin-top: 0.8rem; font-size: inherit; max-width: 118.4rem;\"><strong>Art and Science of Drawing Portraits</strong>&nbsp;- You will learn about the anatomy and structure of the eye and mouth before learning how to accurately draw them, either from imagination or from a subject. You will also learn how to draw a realistic nose, hair, and ears, before producing the final project in this course, a portrait. As you draw the portrait, you will apply various methods you have learned throughout the course, including gesture, line, block-in, structural drawing, and applying tone or value.</p><p style=\"margin-top: 0.8rem; font-size: inherit; max-width: 118.4rem;\"><strong>Enroll now and get started producing amazing, beautiful drawings!&nbsp;We\'ll see you in the course. There is a 30-day money-back guarantee, so if you don\'t like the course, you can get a refund. But we know you\'ll love this course, as you produce awesome drawings in this complete drawing course.</strong></p>', '{\"0\":\"Beginner Level knowledge of PHP\\/Laravel is required\",\"2\":\"Beginner Level knowledge of Vue is required\"}', '{\"0\":\"Learn how to Build Single Page Applications using Laravel 11, Inertia and Vue 3\",\"2\":\"Learn how to Build dependent dropdowns in Laravel and Vue\",\"3\":\"Learn how to build a Multiple Drag and Drop File Uploading and Processing with Laravel\\/Inertia\\/Vue\",\"4\":\"Learn how to implement Infinite Scrolling in Inertia Based Applications\",\"5\":\"Learn how to Implement Roles and Permissions on an Inertia based App (Without using any external package)\",\"6\":\"Learn how to Build Data-tables using Laravel, Inertia and Vue.\",\"7\":\"Learn how to Implement Translations in an Inertia based app.\",\"8\":\"Learn how to Customize Error Pages in Inertia\"}', '[{\"title\":\"Who is this course designed for?\",\"description\":\"This course is designed for developers who have a basic understanding of Laravel and want to learn how to integrate Inertia.js and Vue 3 to build dynamic, modern web applications.\"},{\"title\":\"What prerequisites do I need before taking this course?\",\"description\":\"You should have a basic understanding of Laravel, PHP, and JavaScript. Familiarity with Vue.js and the basics of front-end development (HTML, CSS) is also recommended.\"},{\"title\":\"What will I learn in this course?\",\"description\":\"ou will learn how to set up a Laravel 11 project with Inertia.js and Vue 3, manage state with Vuex, create and manage components, handle routing and authentication, and build a complete SPA (Single Page Application).\"},{\"title\":\"How is this course structured?\",\"description\":\"The course is divided into modules that cover setting up your development environment, understanding Inertia.js, integrating Vue 3, managing state, creating components, and building a full-fledged SPA. Each module includes video lectures, practical exercises, and projects.\"},{\"title\":\"Will I receive a certificate upon completion?\",\"description\":\"Yes, you will receive a certificate of completion after successfully finishing the course, which you can share with potential employers or on professional networking sites.\"},{\"title\":\"How can I get help if I have questions or need assistance?\",\"description\":\"You can ask questions and seek assistance through the course\\u2019s Q&A section or community forum, where instructors and fellow students can provide guidance and support.\"},{\"title\":\"Can I access the course materials after completing the course?\",\"description\":\"Yes, once you enroll, you will have lifetime access to all course materials, including any future updates.\"},{\"title\":\"What resources are included in the course?\",\"description\":\"The course includes video tutorials, downloadable resources, practical exercises, quizzes, and project files. Additionally, you will have access to a community forum for support and collaboration.\"},{\"title\":\"Are there any projects or hands-on exercises in the course?\",\"description\":\"Yes, the course includes numerous hands-on exercises and real-world projects that help you apply the concepts learned and build practical experience in using Laravel, Inertia.js, and Vue 3.\"},{\"title\":\"Do I need any special software or tools for this course?\",\"description\":\"You will need a computer with internet access, a code editor (such as Visual Studio Code), a local development environment (such as XAMPP or MAMP), and Composer. Detailed setup instructions are provided in the course.\"},{\"title\":\"How long will it take to complete the course?\",\"description\":\"The course is self-paced, so the duration depends on your schedule and learning speed. On average, students can expect to spend several weeks to a few months completing the course and mastering the content.\"},{\"title\":\"Is this course suitable for someone with no programming experience?\",\"description\":\"This course is best suited for those who have some basic experience with Laravel and JavaScript. If you\'re completely new to programming, it might be beneficial to start with introductory courses on Laravel and JavaScript first.\"}]', '[\"1\"]', 0, '2025-01-01 09:06:47', '2025-01-01 09:06:47', NULL, NULL, NULL),
