(265, 'After Effects Motion Graphics', 'after-effects-motion-graphics-265', 'This course by focusing on animation covers every technique of Motion Graphics in After Effects.', 1, 27, 'general', NULL, NULL, 'active', 'advanced', 'english', 1, 0, 69, 49, 1, '', NULL, 'uploads/course-thumbnail/-1722153358.jpg', 'uploads/course-banner/-1722320044.jpg', NULL, '<p style=\"font-size: inherit; max-width: 118.4rem;\"><strong>Have you ever asked yourself why some seemingly simple videos have such astonishing animations, while some other ones are a pain to watch?</strong></p><p style=\"margin-top: 0.8rem; font-size: inherit; max-width: 118.4rem;\">That’s because many beginner animators aren’t familiar with the principles of animation or animation theory in general, they don’t know what aspects they should focus on to improve their work, why those are important, and how they should implement such things in their animations.</p><p style=\"margin-top: 0.8rem; font-size: inherit; max-width: 118.4rem;\">In this course,&nbsp;<strong>we will dive into the depths of After effects</strong>. you will learn everything from the&nbsp;<strong>most basic animation techniques to the most advanced ones practically</strong>, so you can achieve astounding results.</p><p style=\"margin-top: 0.8rem; font-size: inherit; max-width: 118.4rem;\">What’s more, our journey will not end until I see you becoming a pro motion designer.&nbsp;<strong>So, this course is suitable for both beginners and veterans.</strong></p><p style=\"margin-top: 0.8rem; font-size: inherit; max-width: 118.4rem;\"><br></p><p style=\"margin-top: 0.8rem; font-size: inherit; max-width: 118.4rem;\"><strong>Let’s see What are you gonna learn during this course?</strong></p><p style=\"margin-top: 0.8rem; font-size: inherit; max-width: 118.4rem;\"><br></p><ul style=\"margin-top: 0.8rem; padding-left: 2.4rem; font-size: inherit; max-width: 118.4rem;\"><li style=\"padding-left: 0.8rem;\"><p style=\"font-size: inherit; max-width: 118.4rem;\">Since our goal is to create motion graphics and the best software for that is after effects, firstly,&nbsp;<strong>you’ll get familiar with \'after-effects\' and required tools for animation</strong>&nbsp;and further on, you\'ll&nbsp;<strong>learn how key frames and graphs work</strong>.</p></li></ul><ul style=\"padding-left: 2.4rem; font-size: inherit; max-width: 118.4rem;\"><li style=\"padding-left: 0.8rem;\"><p style=\"font-size: inherit; max-width: 118.4rem;\">And for a better understanding of timing, spacing, and easing which are the most important principles of animation,&nbsp;<strong>we\'ll do a couple of jumping ball exercises</strong>&nbsp;that are the most essential practices for getting to know these principles.</p><p style=\"margin-top: 0.8rem; font-size: inherit; max-width: 118.4rem;\"><br></p></li><li style=\"margin-top: 0.4rem; padding-left: 0.8rem;\"><p style=\"font-size: inherit; max-width: 118.4rem;\">Our next step would be the&nbsp;<strong>12 main principles of animation</strong>&nbsp;which will be used to spice up the animations and you\'ll learn how to use them in your works properly.</p></li></ul><ul style=\"padding-left: 2.4rem; font-size: inherit; max-width: 118.4rem;\"><li style=\"padding-left: 0.8rem;\"><p style=\"font-size: inherit; max-width: 118.4rem;\">Moving on, you\'ll learn how to work with&nbsp;<strong>Text layers</strong>&nbsp;and how you can&nbsp;<strong>create amazing text animations</strong>.</p></li></ul><ul style=\"padding-left: 2.4rem; font-size: inherit; max-width: 118.4rem;\"><li style=\"padding-left: 0.8rem;\"><p style=\"font-size: inherit; max-width: 118.4rem;\">Afterward, learning&nbsp;<strong>Lettering animations</strong>&nbsp;and their respective principles are in our journey and we\'re going to create a mind-blowing lettering animation.</p></li></ul><ul style=\"padding-left: 2.4rem; font-size: inherit; max-width: 118.4rem;\"><li style=\"padding-left: 0.8rem;\"><p style=\"font-size: inherit; max-width: 118.4rem;\">In the next chapter, we\'ll spend some time on&nbsp;<strong>Loop animations</strong>&nbsp;and the principles of creating one, and how to use them to create a beautiful work of such.</p></li></ul><ul style=\"padding-left: 2.4rem; font-size: inherit; max-width: 118.4rem;\"><li style=\"padding-left: 0.8rem;\"><p style=\"font-size: inherit; max-width: 118.4rem;\">Then you\'ll learn about&nbsp;<strong>Morph animation</strong>. you\'ll learn how to create an exquisite morph animation, alongside following a proper set of rules.</p></li></ul><ul style=\"padding-left: 2.4rem; font-size: inherit; max-width: 118.4rem;\"><li style=\"padding-left: 0.8rem;\"><p style=\"font-size: inherit; max-width: 118.4rem;\">In the next chapter, you\'ll learn the types of&nbsp;<strong>Logo animations</strong>, methods and rules of making them, and also how to give them sense.</p></li></ul><ul style=\"padding-left: 2.4rem; font-size: inherit; max-width: 118.4rem;\"><li style=\"padding-left: 0.8rem;\"><p style=\"font-size: inherit; max-width: 118.4rem;\">In the next chapter, you\'ll get familiar with one of the most challenging topics of animations yet the simplest one which is&nbsp;<strong>Character rigging</strong>. In this chapter, you\'ll&nbsp;<strong>learn about the Duik Bassel script and the required tools for rigging characters</strong>, from the most basic topic that is preparing the character to rigging a character.</p></li></ul><ul style=\"padding-left: 2.4rem; font-size: inherit; max-width: 118.4rem;\"><li style=\"padding-left: 0.8rem;\"><p style=\"font-size: inherit; max-width: 118.4rem;\">After you\'ve learned to rig, we will work on&nbsp;<strong>Animating the character</strong>&nbsp;and how to use references properly so we can get better results.</p></li></ul><ul style=\"padding-left: 2.4rem; font-size: inherit; max-width: 118.4rem;\"><li style=\"padding-left: 0.8rem;\"><p style=\"font-size: inherit; max-width: 118.4rem;\">After that, we\'ll work on&nbsp;<strong>Rigging the head</strong>&nbsp;and different parts of the face then we\'ll start animating the head and create different emotions for the face.</p></li></ul><p style=\"margin-top: 0.8rem; font-size: inherit; max-width: 118.4rem;\"><br></p><p style=\"margin-top: 0.8rem; font-size: inherit; max-width: 118.4rem;\"><strong>This course is focused on doing projects</strong>, which means you\'ll learn whatever you need to know through action, and at the same time, you create beautiful animations and motion graphics that can be very effective in showing your portfolio&nbsp; powerfully.</p><p style=\"margin-top: 0.8rem; font-size: inherit; max-width: 118.4rem;\"><strong>This&nbsp; course is the product of years of my experience in motion graphics</strong>&nbsp;and It\'s here for you so you can become a veteran in motion graphics as quickly as possible and&nbsp;<strong>so you won\'t make the same mistakes as I did</strong>.</p><p style=\"margin-top: 0.8rem; font-size: inherit; max-width: 118.4rem;\"><br></p><p style=\"margin-top: 0.8rem; font-size: inherit; max-width: 118.4rem;\"><strong>I\'ll be here for you in every step until you become a pro motion designer.</strong></p><p style=\"margin-top: 0.8rem; font-size: inherit; max-width: 118.4rem;\">So, register now and take your skills to the next level</p>', '{\"0\":\"Beginner Level knowledge of PHP\\/Laravel is required\",\"2\":\"Beginner Level knowledge of Vue is required\"}', '{\"0\":\"Learn how to Build Single Page Applications using Laravel 11, Inertia and Vue 3\",\"2\":\"Learn how to Build dependent dropdowns in Laravel and Vue\",\"3\":\"Learn how to build a Multiple Drag and Drop File Uploading and Processing with Laravel\\/Inertia\\/Vue\",\"4\":\"Learn how to implement Infinite Scrolling in Inertia Based Applications\",\"5\":\"Learn how to Implement Roles and Permissions on an Inertia based App (Without using any external package)\",\"6\":\"Learn how to Build Data-tables using Laravel, Inertia and Vue.\",\"7\":\"Learn how to Implement Translations in an Inertia based app.\",\"8\":\"Learn how to Customize Error Pages in Inertia\"}', '[{\"title\":\"Who is this course designed for?\",\"description\":\"This course is designed for developers who have a basic understanding of Laravel and want to learn how to integrate Inertia.js and Vue 3 to build dynamic, modern web applications.\"},{\"title\":\"What prerequisites do I need before taking this course?\",\"description\":\"You should have a basic understanding of Laravel, PHP, and JavaScript. Familiarity with Vue.js and the basics of front-end development (HTML, CSS) is also recommended.\"},{\"title\":\"What will I learn in this course?\",\"description\":\"ou will learn how to set up a Laravel 11 project with Inertia.js and Vue 3, manage state with Vuex, create and manage components, handle routing and authentication, and build a complete SPA (Single Page Application).\"},{\"title\":\"How is this course structured?\",\"description\":\"The course is divided into modules that cover setting up your development environment, understanding Inertia.js, integrating Vue 3, managing state, creating components, and building a full-fledged SPA. Each module includes video lectures, practical exercises, and projects.\"},{\"title\":\"Will I receive a certificate upon completion?\",\"description\":\"Yes, you will receive a certificate of completion after successfully finishing the course, which you can share with potential employers or on professional networking sites.\"},{\"title\":\"How can I get help if I have questions or need assistance?\",\"description\":\"You can ask questions and seek assistance through the course\\u2019s Q&A section or community forum, where instructors and fellow students can provide guidance and support.\"},{\"title\":\"Can I access the course materials after completing the course?\",\"description\":\"Yes, once you enroll, you will have lifetime access to all course materials, including any future updates.\"},{\"title\":\"What resources are included in the course?\",\"description\":\"The course includes video tutorials, downloadable resources, practical exercises, quizzes, and project files. Additionally, you will have access to a community forum for support and collaboration.\"},{\"title\":\"Are there any projects or hands-on exercises in the course?\",\"description\":\"Yes, the course includes numerous hands-on exercises and real-world projects that help you apply the concepts learned and build practical experience in using Laravel, Inertia.js, and Vue 3.\"},{\"title\":\"Do I need any special software or tools for this course?\",\"description\":\"You will need a computer with internet access, a code editor (such as Visual Studio Code), a local development environment (such as XAMPP or MAMP), and Composer. Detailed setup instructions are provided in the course.\"},{\"title\":\"How long will it take to complete the course?\",\"description\":\"The course is self-paced, so the duration depends on your schedule and learning speed. On average, students can expect to spend several weeks to a few months completing the course and mastering the content.\"},{\"title\":\"Is this course suitable for someone with no programming experience?\",\"description\":\"This course is best suited for those who have some basic experience with Laravel and JavaScript. If you\'re completely new to programming, it might be beneficial to start with introductory courses on Laravel and JavaScript first.\"}]', '[\"1\"]', 0, '2025-01-01 09:06:47', '2025-01-01 09:06:47', NULL, NULL, NULL),
