n how to purchase quality designs from trusted designers, but also how to easily create your own designs with easy to use tools and thousands of pre-made t-shirt design templates.</p><p style=\"margin-top: 0.8rem; font-size: inherit; max-width: 118.4rem;\"><br></p><p style=\"margin-top: 0.8rem; font-size: inherit; max-width: 118.4rem;\"><strong>Sales Channels &amp; Marketplaces</strong></p><p style=\"margin-top: 0.8rem; font-size: inherit; max-width: 118.4rem;\"><br></p><p style=\"margin-top: 0.8rem; font-size: inherit; max-width: 118.4rem;\">We will go over how to create professional t-shirt designs, and get started on several print on demand marketplaces such Redbubble and Spring (among others). You can start by setting up your ecommerce store on one platform, and have the ability to create additional income streams as you build your brand and expand to other marketplaces.</p><p style=\"margin-top: 0.8rem; font-size: inherit; max-width: 118.4rem;\"><br></p><p style=\"margin-top: 0.8rem; font-size: inherit; max-width: 118.4rem;\">By leveraging print-on-demand marketplaces to start your print-on-demand t shirt business, you can focus all of your attention on creating great designs for your products, and let the marketplace handle the inventory storage, production, and shipping.</p><p style=\"margin-top: 0.8rem; font-size: inherit; max-width: 118.4rem;\"><br style=\"color: rgb(45, 47, 49); font-family: &quot;Udemy Sans&quot;, &quot;SF Pro Text&quot;, -apple-system, &quot;system-ui&quot;, Roboto, &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif, &quot;Apple Color Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Symbol&quot;;\"></p>', '{\"0\":\"Beginner Level knowledge of PHP\\/Laravel is required\",\"2\":\"Beginner Level knowledge of Vue is required\"}', '{\"0\":\"Learn how to Build Single Page Applications using Laravel 11, Inertia and Vue 3\",\"2\":\"Learn how to Build dependent dropdowns in Laravel and Vue\",\"3\":\"Learn how to build a Multiple Drag and Drop File Uploading and Processing with Laravel\\/Inertia\\/Vue\",\"4\":\"Learn how to implement Infinite Scrolling in Inertia Based Applications\",\"5\":\"Learn how to Implement Roles and Permissions on an Inertia based App (Without using any external package)\",\"6\":\"Learn how to Build Data-tables using Laravel, Inertia and Vue.\",\"7\":\"Learn how to Implement Translations in an Inertia based app.\",\"8\":\"Learn how to Customize Error Pages in Inertia\"}', '[{\"title\":\"Who is this course designed for?\",\"description\":\"This course is designed for developers who have a basic understanding of Laravel and want to learn how to integrate Inertia.js and Vue 3 to build dynamic, modern web applications.\"},{\"title\":\"What prerequisites do I need before taking this course?\",\"description\":\"You should have a basic understanding of Laravel, PHP, and JavaScript. Familiarity with Vue.js and the basics of front-end development (HTML, CSS) is also recommended.\"},{\"title\":\"What will I learn in this course?\",\"description\":\"ou will learn how to set up a Laravel 11 project with Inertia.js and Vue 3, manage state with Vuex, create and manage components, handle routing and authentication, and build a complete SPA (Single Page Application).\"},{\"title\":\"How is this course structured?\",\"description\":\"The course is divided into modules that cover setting up your development environment, understanding Inertia.js, integrating Vue 3, managing state, creating components, and building a full-fledged SPA. Each module includes video lectures, practical exercises, and projects.\"},{\"title\":\"Will I receive a certificate upon completion?\",\"description\":\"Yes, you will receive a certificate of completion after successfully finishing the course, which you can share with potential employers or on professional networking sites.\"},{\"title\":\"How can I get help if I have questions or need assistance?\",\"description\":\"You can ask questions and seek assistance through the course\\u2019s Q&A section or community forum, where instructors and fellow students can provide guidance and support.\"},{\"title\":\"Can I access the course materials after completing the course?\",\"description\":\"Yes, once you enroll, you will have lifetime access to all course materials, including any future updates.\"},{\"title\":\"What resources are included in the course?\",\"description\":\"The course includes video tutorials, downloadable resources, practical exercises, quizzes, and project files. Additionally, you will have access to a community forum for support and collaboration.\"},{\"title\":\"Are there any projects or hands-on exercises in the course?\",\"description\":\"Yes, the course includes numerous hands-on exercises and real-world projects that help you apply the concepts learned and build practical experience in using Laravel, Inertia.js, and Vue 3.\"},{\"title\":\"Do I need any special software or tools for this course?\",\"description\":\"You will need a computer with internet access, a code editor (such as Visual Studio Code), a local development environment (such as XAMPP or MAMP), and Composer. Detailed setup instructions are provided in the course.\"},{\"title\":\"How long will it take to complete the course?\",\"description\":\"The course is self-paced, so the duration depends on your schedule and learning speed. On average, students can expect to spend several weeks to a few months completing the course and mastering the content.\"},{\"title\":\"Is this course suitable for someone with no programming experience?\",\"description\":\"This course is best suited for those who have some basic experience with Laravel and JavaScript. If you\'re completely new to programming, it might be beneficial to start with introductory courses on Laravel and JavaScript first.\"}]', '[\"1\"]', 0, '2025-01-01 09:06:47', '2025-01-01 09:06:47', NULL, NULL, NULL);
